{"id":14880828,"mediaExerciseId":"831bbe0a-d384-42c2-899b-87bcea36e3d8","exerciseName":"2","chapterName":"3","chapterTitle":"Working with Financial Statements","groupId":612277,"groupTitle":"Minicase Questions","isPremium":true,"sectionName":null,"sectionTitle":null,"pageNumber":90,"solutions":[{"id":6357705,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"In this problem, we will determine whether the given company is a good aspirant company. ","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"Choosing an aspirant company means that this company should be able to perform and compete at the same level as your company. This means that the target market and the amount of time it takes to produce the products are almost the same. ","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2},{"columns":[{"text":"We cannot choose Boeing as an aspirant company because it produces large aircrafts while our company is in the light aircraft business. This means that the target market for the two companies are completely different since Boeing caters to airlines and military services while our company caters to individuals that want a private jet. ","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":3},{"columns":[{"text":"The first two companies listed cannot be used as an aspirant company also for the same reason. Therefore, we can only choose between Cirrus and Cessna as they have production lines that cater to the same target market as us. ","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":4}],"rating":0,"solutionUuid":"06a15086-2abf-48e5-998d-37ccc90332a0","editorVersion":2,"answeredOn":null,"ratingCount":null,"solutionOrder":null,"totalSteps":4}],"textbook":{"authors":"Br